        <h2>Performance Marketing</h2>
        <h3>What is Performance Marketing?</h3>
        <p>
          Performance marketing is a digital marketing strategy where
          advertisers pay only when specific actions (such as clicks, leads, or
          sales) are completed. It focuses on measurable outcomes and optimizes
          campaigns based on real-time data.
        </p>

        <h3>How does Performance Marketing work?</h3>
        <p>
          Performance marketing works by using platforms such as Google Ads,
          social media, and affiliate marketing networks. Advertisers set a goal
          (e.g., increasing sales or leads) and pay when that goal is achieved.
          The success of these campaigns is tracked using performance metrics
          like cost-per-click (CPC), cost-per-action (CPA), or return on ad
          spend (ROAS).
        </p>

        <h3>What are the key channels used in Performance Marketing?</h3>
        <p>
          Key channels in performance marketing include search engine marketing
          (SEM), social media advertising, display ads, affiliate marketing, and
          email marketing. These channels are optimized based on user behavior
          to achieve specific marketing goals.
        </p>

        <h3>What are the benefits of Performance Marketing?</h3>
        <p>
          The main benefits of performance marketing are cost efficiency,
          transparency, and data-driven decision-making. Advertisers can control
          their budgets, target specific audiences, and get measurable results,
          which helps in maximizing ROI.
        </p>

        <h3>
          What is the difference between Performance Marketing and Traditional
          Marketing?
        </h3>
        <p>
          Traditional marketing involves paying upfront for advertising
          regardless of the outcome, whereas performance marketing only charges
          advertisers when a specific action is taken, such as a click,
          conversion, or sale. This makes performance marketing more
          cost-effective and measurable.
        </p>

        <h3>How can I track the success of Performance Marketing campaigns?</h3>
        <p>
          The success of performance marketing campaigns can be tracked using
          tools like Google Analytics, conversion tracking, and specialized
          marketing dashboards. Key performance indicators (KPIs) such as
          click-through rates (CTR), cost-per-lead (CPL), and return on
          investment (ROI) are commonly used to measure success.
        </p>

        <h3>What is the role of data in Performance Marketing?</h3>
        <p>
          Data plays a crucial role in performance marketing by helping
          advertisers optimize campaigns in real-time. It enables marketers to
          track customer behavior, refine targeting strategies, and improve ROI
          through personalized and relevant messaging.
        </p>

        <h3>What is affiliate marketing in Performance Marketing?</h3>
        <p>
          Affiliate marketing is a type of performance marketing where partners
          (affiliates) promote a business's products or services in exchange for
          a commission. Affiliates are only paid when they successfully drive a
          sale, lead, or other defined action.
        </p>
      </div>
