          <h2>Web Development</h2>

          <h3>What is web development?</h3>
          <p>
            Web development involves creating and maintaining websites or web
            applications. It includes tasks like coding, designing, and managing
            the functionality, user experience, and performance of a website
            across various devices and platforms.
          </p>

          <h3>
            What is the difference between front-end and back-end development?
          </h3>
          <p>
            Front-end development focuses on the user interface and experience
            of a website, including layout, design, and interaction. Back-end
            development handles the server-side logic, databases, and APIs that
            make the website functional.
          </p>

          <h3>Why is responsive web design important?</h3>
          <p>
            Responsive web design ensures that a website adapts seamlessly to
            different screen sizes and devices, providing an optimal user
            experience on desktops, tablets, and smartphones. It improves user
            engagement and helps with SEO rankings.
          </p>

          <h3>How long does it take to develop a website?</h3>
          <p>
            The time it takes to develop a website depends on its complexity. A
            simple website can take a few weeks, while a complex web application
            with custom features may take several months. Proper planning and
            testing are essential to ensure a successful launch.
          </p>

          <h3>What is the importance of website speed in web development?</h3>
          <p>
            Website speed is crucial in web development as it directly affects
            user experience, bounce rates, and SEO rankings. A fast-loading
            website keeps visitors engaged, reduces abandonment rates, and
            improves search engine performance.
          </p>

          <h3>How does SEO impact web development?</h3>
          <p>
            SEO (Search Engine Optimization) impacts web development by
            influencing how a website is built and structured. Developers ensure
            that the site is fast, mobile-friendly, and follows best practices
            in code structure, all of which help improve search engine rankings.
          </p>

          <h3>What are the security best practices in web development?</h3>
          <p>
            Security best practices in web development include using HTTPS,
            regularly updating software, implementing strong password policies,
            encrypting data, and protecting against threats like SQL injections,
            cross-site scripting (XSS), and DDoS attacks.
          </p>
        </div>
